                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/2455a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the Commission of Neutrals (<persName
                            corresp="#p_WF1" type="from">White</persName>) to the <gloss type="to"
                            >Secretary of State</gloss>, at Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-10-26">October 26,
                            1932</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Bolivia accepted this afternoon neutral proposal already accepted by Paraguay
                    that the two delegates enter into a conference under the auspices of the Neutral
                    Commission to stop hostilities and settle Chaco dispute. First meeting will take
                    place at 3 o’clock tomorrow afternoon. Above released to press.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
